## Gap Analysis: Your Sub-Phases Are Incomplete

Your sub-phases 2.4 and 2.5 cover **generic habit completion** (mark as done/missed) and **streaks/freezes/dashboard** — but they **completely miss** making `numeric`, `timer`, and `checklist` types functional. Here's what's missing:

| Type | Your sub-phases cover this? | What's actually needed |
|---|---|---|
| **boolean** | ✅ Yes — `status: completed` in `habit_logs` | Nothing extra |
| **numeric** | ❌ No | `habit_logs.value` column + "I did 5 out of 8" input UI |
| **timer** | ❌ No | `habit_logs.duration_seconds` column + stopwatch UI component |
| **checklist** | ❌ No | `habit_checklist_items` table + draggable checklist UI |

Without addressing these, `numeric`/`timer`/`checklist` remain empty shells — users pay to unlock them but get zero functionality beyond a label.

---

## Complete Phased Plan (Single Source of Truth)

### PHASE 1: Database Schema — Type-Specific Log Support

**Goal:** Make `habit_logs` capable of storing data for all 4 types.

| Action | Details |
|---|---|
| Add `value` column | `DECIMAL(10,2) NULL` — for numeric logs (e.g., `5.00` glasses) |
| Add `duration_seconds` column | `INT NULL` — for timer logs (e.g., `932` seconds = 15:32) |
| Create `habit_checklist_items` table | `id`, `habit_id` (FK), `title` (string), `sort_order` (int) |
| Create `habit_checklist_logs` table | `id`, `habit_log_id` (FK), `checklist_item_id` (FK), `is_checked` (bool) |
| Create `streaks` table | `id`, `user_id`, `habit_id`, `current_streak` (int), `longest_streak` (int), `last_log_date` (date) |
| Create `streak_freezes` table | `id`, `user_id`, `habit_id`, `frozen_date` (date), unique(`user_id`, `habit_id`, `frozen_date`) |

**Files to create:**
- `database/migrations/xxxx_add_type_columns_to_habit_logs.php`
- `database/migrations/xxxx_create_habit_checklist_items_table.php`
- `database/migrations/xxxx_create_habit_checklist_logs_table.php`
- `database/migrations/xxxx_create_streaks_table.php`
- `database/migrations/xxxx_create_streak_freezes_table.php`

---

### PHASE 2: Backend — Habit Type CRUD + Logging

**Goal:** Users can define type-specific data when creating habits, and log type-specific data when completing them.

| Build | Business Logic |
|---|---|
| `HabitChecklistItem` model | BelongsTo `Habit`, has `title` + `sort_order` |
| Update `Habit` model | HasMany `checklistItems`, update `$fillable` |
| Update `HabitResource` | Include `checklist_items` when type is `checklist` |
| Update `StoreHabitRequest` | Validate `checklist_items` array when type is `checklist` |
| Update `UpdateHabitRequest` | Same, with `sometimes` |
| Update `HabitService` | Sync checklist items (similar to how tags are synced) |
| `HabitLog` model | Add `value`, `duration_seconds` to `$fillable` and `$casts` |
| `HabitLogService` | `logCompletion()` — handles boolean/numeric/timer/checklist differently |
| `HabitLogController` | `store` (log a habit), `update` (modify log), `destroy` (remove log) |
| `HabitLogResource` | Type-aware response — includes `value`, `duration`, `checklist_logs` |
| Routes | `POST /api/user/habits/{id}/logs`, `PUT /api/user/habit-logs/{id}` |

**Files to create/modify:**
- `app/Models/HabitChecklistItem.php` (new)
- `app/Models/HabitLog.php` (modify — add fillable/casts)
- `app/Services/User/Habit/HabitLogService.php` (new)
- `app/Http/Controllers/User/HabitLogController.php` (new)
- `app/Http/Resources/User/HabitLogResource.php` (new)
- `app/Http/Requests/User/HabitLog/StoreHabitLogRequest.php` (new)
- `app/Http/Requests/User/HabitLog/UpdateHabitLogRequest.php` (new)
- Modify: `Habit.php`, `HabitResource.php`, `StoreHabitRequest.php`, `UpdateHabitRequest.php`, `HabitService.php`
- `routes/api.php` (add log routes)

---

### PHASE 3: Backend — Streaks & Freezes

**Goal:** Automatic streak calculation and quota-aware freeze system.

| Build | Business Logic |
|---|---|
| `Streak` model | BelongsTo User, BelongsTo Habit |
| `StreakFreeze` model | BelongsTo User, BelongsTo Habit |
| `StreakService` | `calculate(Habit)`, `recalculate(Habit)`, `applyFreeze(Habit, date)` |
| `HabitLogObserver` | On log created/updated/deleted → trigger `StreakService::recalculate()` |
| `StreakFreezeController` | `store` — checks `PlanQuotaService::getLimit(user, 'max_freezes_per_week')` |
| `habits:mark-missed` command | Runs every 15 min, finds habits due yesterday with `pending` status → set `missed` |
| Update `HabitResource` | Include `streak` relationship |

**Files to create/modify:**
- `app/Models/Streak.php` (new)
- `app/Models/StreakFreeze.php` (new)
- `app/Services/User/Habit/StreakService.php` (new)
- `app/Observers/HabitLogObserver.php` (new)
- `app/Http/Controllers/User/StreakFreezeController.php` (new)
- `app/Http/Requests/User/StreakFreeze/StoreStreakFreezeRequest.php` (new)
- `app/Console/Commands/MarkMissedHabits.php` (new)
- `app/Providers/AppServiceProvider.php` (register observer)
- `routes/console.php` (add mark-missed schedule)
- Modify: `HabitResource.php`

